    "The most evident symptoms of plant diseases to the human eye are spots on the leaves.",
    "On the other hand, some diseases do not manifest themselves on the leaves.",
    "In contrast, others manifest themselves in the latter stages and after the plants have already suffered significant damage.",
    "Timely management of major crops necessitates careful oversight, including monitoring for diseases that could turn them into waste and addressing various issues promptly.",
    "Diseases can diminish plant productivity, and since each plant is susceptible to unique diseases, managing them with conventional disease control methods demands significant effort and skilled personnel."
